      Title: Create MCP server skeleton with stdio protocol

      Body:
      TL;DR
      -----
      Implements the core MCP server skeleton with stdio protocol support

      Details
      -------
      This implementation creates the foundation for the MBTA MCP server by setting up the core server infrastructure:

      - Adds the mcp-go dependency for the Machine Control Protocol implementation
      - Creates a server package with proper initialization and configuration
      - Implements request handlers for transit information queries
      - Adds basic logging middleware for request tracking
      - Sets up stdio protocol handling for communication

      The server follows the Model Context Protocol (MCP) specification to enable AI assistants to query MBTA transit information. At this stage, the implementation
      provides a skeleton with mock data responses. Future PR's will implement the actual MBTA API client integration.

      This PR completes Phase 1, Step 1.3 in the implementation plan: "MCP Server Skeleton".

